-- RBS Said to Sell $1.2 Billion of Credit Card-Backed Bonds
-- B y   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-01-13T17:43:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/rbs-said-to-sell-1-2-billion-of-credit-card-backed-bonds.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) 
priced $1.2 billion of bonds backed by U.K. credit cards after
initially seeking $500 million, according to a banker involved
in the transaction.  The securities with an average life of 1.49 years were
priced at 70 basis points more than one-month Libor, the banker
said. The bonds were issued through Arran Cards Funding Plc
2012-1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
